NavMesh Enemy Navigation
in the toolbar, click on Window > AI > Navigation. (this will open up a new tool) 
Click on Object (in the new tool window) and select the surface in the scene. 
Check Navigation static and make sure "Walkable" is selected for the 'Navigation Area' drop-down. 
Now click on the walls in your scene, check static and change to Not Walkable. Now go to the "Bake" tab, on the left of 'Object' and click bake. 
If your Agent is clipping through the walls, you can always increase "Agent Radius" in the Bake Tab.
